The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Student arson 
                                                                                                               Student arson 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Burdwan, Aug. 31: Around 200 Burdwan University students fought with police today after a bus ran over a youth coming for classes.         
	At 10.40, when Subhodeep Ghosh of Chinsurah was on his way to the University Institute of Technology, the bus hit his cycle from the back. He died on the spot.         
	The colleges students  Subhodeep was a second-year student of bachelor of computer applications  blocked the GT Road demanding that the bus driver, who had fled, be arrested. They hurled bricks and soft drink bottles at the police when they tried to take away the body. After 40 minutes, the police managed to take the body away.        
	In order to calm the area  it is close to Burdwan University to which the college is affiliated  reinforcements arrived but the students started throwing stones again, prompting another batoncharge and lobbing of tear-gas shells.                                                                                                                                                                              
